  "text": "LC-MS conditions were as described by Samuelsson et al. [CITATION_1] . Lipid extracts were separated on an Acquity CSH C 18 column (100 ϫ 2.1 mm, 1.7-m inner diameter; Waters, Milford, MA) at 65°C using a gradient elution program at a flow rate of 600 l/min. The mobile phase consisted of acetonitrile-water-formic acid (59.95:39.95:0.1 vol/vol ϩ 10 mM ammonium formate; solvent A) and isopropyl alcohol-acetonitrile-formic acid (99.95:9.95:0.1 vol/vol ϩ 10 mM ammonium formate; solvent B) using the following elution program: 85-70% A (0 -2 min), 70 -52% A (2-2.5 min), 52-18% A (2.5-11 min), 18 -1% A (11-11.5 min), 1% A (11.5-12 min), 1-85% A (12-12.1 min), and 85% A (12.1-15 min). Column effluent was connected to an electrospray source of a high-resolution mass spectrometer (Q-Exactive Orbitrap; Thermo), and mass spectral data were collected in profile data acquisition mode covering a mass range of m/z ϭ 200 -2,000 with a mass resolution setting of 35,000 and a maximum trap fill time of 250 ms using the Xcalibur software package. A data-dependent MS 2 (ddMS 2 ) fragment analysis using the same settings was performed on every 10th sample to facilitate identification.",
